1. Concurrency & Parallel Programming
✅ Concept:
Concurrency: Multiple tasks run logically together (not necessarily same time)
Parallelism: Tasks run at the same time (using multiple CPU cores)
✅ In Python:
Async (asyncio) → best for APIs
Threading → I/O tasks
Multiprocessing → CPU-heavy tasks
✅ Example:
import asyncio

async def task():
    await asyncio.sleep(1)
    return "Done"

async def main():
    result = await asyncio.gather(task(), task())
    print(result)

asyncio.run(main())
✅ Use in Project:

✔ Fast API handling multiple users simultaneously

